  "recipeInstructions": [
    "Cut the cucumbers in half lengthways and scoop out the seeds with a teaspoon. Cut each half on an angle into l -2cm thick slices.",
    "Heat a ridged griddle pan or heavy-based frying pan over a medium-high heat. Season the lamb chops with salt and pepper, brush with oil and cook for about 5 minutes on each side, keeping them pink.",
    "Meanwhile, heat the rapeseed 011 in another frying pan and add the shallots. Fry, stirring, for a minute, then add the cucumber slices. Season with salt and pepper and saute over a fairly high heat for 2-3 minutes until tender. Take off the heat and stir in the shredded mint.",
    "Divide the cucumber between warmed plates and place the lamb chops on top to serve"
  ],
